  "prompt": "What is the meaning of Hindi word \u2018\u092d\u0947\u0926\u092d\u093e\u0935\u2019 (Bhedbhaav)?",
  "response": "The Hindi word \"\u092d\u0947\u0926\u092d\u093e\u0935\" (Bhedbhaav) translates to \"discrimination\" in English. It refers to the unjust or prejudicial treatment of different categories of people, often based on characteristics such as race, age, gender, or caste. It signifies a difference in treatment or perception and is generally considered a negative practice that contributes to inequality.",
